      {
        "id": 1815263,
        "name": "Ryan Caughey",
        "username": "RyanC",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ryanc/{size}/731_2.png",
        "created_at": "2015-12-16T21:06:54.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Grand_Cru_Cru\" data-username=\"lleichtman\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/lleichtman/48/2332_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> lleichtman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Any experience with this wine. Morrell has it for $95 with free shipping and I have zero experience with this particular wine and only 3 mentions on cellartracker though all good.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I buy this wine virtually every year. It\u2019s consistently excellent, although I haven\u2019t had the '12. That said, $95 is really steep. $65-75 seems to be the going rate.</p>",
