      {
        "id": 1815286,
        "name": "Robert Love",
        "username": "Robert_Love",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/robert_love/{size}/2523_2.png",
        "created_at": "2015-12-16T21:31:50.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-Grand_Cru_Cru\" data-username=\"lleichtman\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/lleichtman/48/2332_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> lleichtman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Any experience with this wine. Morrell has it for $95 with free shipping and I have zero experience with this particular wine and only 3 mentions on cellartracker though all good.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Dauvissat\u2019s La Forest is a gorgeous 1er Chablis. I highly recommend it, although I haven\u2019t had the 2012 yet.</p>\n<p>Note that La Forest is one of the more austere, slower maturing of Dauvissat\u2019s wines, and both Antonio Galloni and Allen Meadows\u2019s TN for the 2012 echo that.</p>\n<p>I\u2019d snag a bottle for that price, but if you are looking to stock up, you can probably find it cheaper.</p>",
